@NODE "SHAREWARE" "AmCEx: How to register"
@NEXT "BUGS"
@PREV "PROGUPDATES"
@TOC "MAIN"


  How to register
  ---------------


    Send the near equivalentą of Ł5 in any major currency to my home
    address below. Only notes can be accepted, and please consider that
    conversion into ukp will cost me too.  Also send a bit more when the
    keyfile has to go on a floppy via snailmail. If in doubt, ask @{"me" LINK "PROGUPDATES"}
    first.

    EuroCheques and UK cheques are acceptable, but will take the usual
    time to clear.

    Sending cash through the post can be risky. For security reasons it
    is best to line the envelope with carbon paper or similar, that way
    the money can not be seen, not even with a strong light behind it.
    Registered mail is always best.

    The registration process will require your name and home address at
    least, and if you have an email address too, the keyfile will be sent
    to you via email.

    It may be easiest to print out the 'Registration.txt' form and fill
    in the details using a pen, or fill it in using EditPad and then
    print it.  In any case, it does have to be signed by hand.  No keyfile
    will be sent without your signature, as that proves that you agree to
    not spreading the keyfile.  If you forget to send it, I will accept
    a PGP signed email stating that agreement.˛

    If you are a poor student and think you can give me a sufficiently
    convincing sob-story of why you cannot afford such a small fee, I may
    let you off.  In this case your PGP signature on your email will be
    acceptable.

    The AmCEx.key goes either into the program directory, or the drawer,
    pointed to by the path held in a KEYPATH environment variable. It will
    immediately unlock all missing features.  Please do not spread this
    keyfile, even 'filthy rich' Amiga developers need to be able to sell
    some to be able to maintain our machines.


                                    P. Juhasz
                                    33 Holmewood Road
                                    London SW2 3RP
                                    U. K.

                                    Tel.: +044 (0)208 674 3242




  ą) i.e. ¤10 or $10 for email delivery, ¤15 or $15 for postal delivery.

  ˛) With email-only registration a PGP signature will be sufficient.



@ENDNODE


@NODE "BUGS" "AmCEx: Undesirables"
@NEXT "CONCLUSION"
@PREV "PROGUPDATES"
@TOC "MAIN"


  Undesired side effects
  ----------------------

  Probably all programs come with bugs.

  1) As AmCEx uses classes/gadgets/string.gadget for the Amount entry,
     the Amount gadget will only accept one '.' as a decimal point
     between the numeric digits you enter.  One day it may be localised
     to accept a comma ',' in lieu of the '.', but maybe noone needs to
     use a comma in this case anyway.

     This filter only works from string.gadget v45 onwards, which came
     with OS3.9, the older versions will allow the user to type in
     letters too, even if the program will reject them.


  2) The window backfill doesn't work too well under OS3.0 and OS3.1, it
     seems to clash with the ListView gadget's background.




@ENDNODE


